      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey can u explain what the principle of least privilege actually means in a business network? like how would u use it in real life?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The principle of least privilege means granting employees and software only the minimum level of access necessary to perform their specific jobs, nothing more. In a real business network, this would involve ensuring that an intern can only access their designated department's servers and that role-based profiles are configured so that a developer can execute code but cannot install new hardware or delete critical business files without superhuman approval. By strictly limiting these permissions, companies significantly reduce the attack surface, making it much harder for hackers or insider threats to move laterally or cause widespread damage if one account is compromised.",
