      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A new marketing person should absolutely never have administrative rights, access to the HR database, or direct entry into the financial server and core code repositories. Over-provisioning flags occur when you grant permissions like read/edit/delete on production databases, ability to install new software on any machine, or visibility into sensitive employee records that go beyond their job description. Giving general user accounts with broad permissions creates dangerous vulnerabilities where a single compromised credential could give an attacker unrestricted access to the entire network infrastructure.",
